    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>General term for rectangular chests used in homes, probably one of the earliest types of home furnishings; in the chest could be stored various items, and it could be used for seating or as a bed as well. For relatively ornate versions of chests, particularly as used in Florentine homes, prefer "cassoni."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
